**Severity:** Critical

**OWASP Top 10 2021 Category:** A1: Broken Access Control

**Description:**

CVE-2017-6168 is a remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability in Apache HTTP Server due to a buffer overflow in the mod_lua module. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the server.

**Solution:**

To fix this issue, apply the following patch:

* Apache HTTP Server 2.4.35 and 2.4.36: https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/mod_lua.html
* Apache HTTP Server 2.2.34 and 2.2.35: https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/mod/mod_lua.html

**Additional Notes:**

* If applying the patch is not possible, disabling the mod_lua module can mitigate the vulnerability.
* It is recommended to keep Apache HTTP Server and its modules up-to-date to prevent future vulnerabilities.
